15/07/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Following talks Monday (14 July) in Sofia, President Georgi Parvanov and his Croatian counterpart, Stipe Mesic, stressed their willingness to co-operate in the Euro-Atlantic integration process. 
Parvanov also expressed Bulgaria's support and readiness to assist Croatia in its preparations for NATO and EU membership. 
"Bulgaria has gone quite a long way towards Europe and we are ready to share our experience with Croatia," he said. 
Mesic later met with Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and senior parliament members. 
Delegations of the two countries signed agreements on co-operation in the social insurance sector, culture and education.
In other news, Kuwaiti official Ali Jabir Al-Ahmad Al-Sabah met with Saxe-Coburg and Foreign Minister Solomon Passy on Monday to discuss the boosting of bilateral ties and regional development. 
He signed an agreement with the governor of Bulgaria's Pazardzhik region, outlining co-operation in trade, tourism, culture and sports, as well as in the organisation of business events and trade exhibitions. 
(BTA, BNT, BBC - 14/07/03)
